  protein: 46 g
---

Peel and finely dice the @red onion{1}(peeled and finely diced) and @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and finely diced). Cut the @red pepper{2} in half, deseed and cut into small cubes. Cut the @celery stick{2} and @courgette{1} into small cubes. Cut the @smoked bacon{5%slices} into small strips.

Dissolve the @chicken stock pot{1} in 600ml of your boiling water in a #bowl{} or #jug{} and set to the side. Add @salt{1/3%tsp} to the remaining water in a #pot{} and cook the @conchiglie pasta{80%g} for ~{8-10%minutes} until al dente.

Whilst the pasta is cooking, heat another #saucepan{} over medium-high heat and add the bacon strips. Cook until crisp and brown on the outside.

Add the @thyme{4%sprigs}, onion, red pepper, garlic and celery and cook for ~{4%minutes} until the vegetables are translucent. Add the courgette and cook for ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add the @bay leaf{1}, stock, @chopped tomatoes{2%400g cans}, @cavolo nero{4%leaves}, @salt{1/3%tsp} and a good grind of @ground black pepper{a good grind}. Cook over medium-low heat for ~{15-20%minutes} or until the vegetables are tender.

Drain and rinse the @organic cannellini beans{2%400g cans} and add to the #saucepan{} along with the cooked and drained conchiglie pasta. Stir everything together and cook for ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Serve the soup into #bowls{} with a tbsp of @fresh pesto{4%tbsp} drizzled over the top of each bowl.